Seven AP officers and two civilians narrowly escaped death when their Land Cruiser plunged into the Indian Ocean a Faza island in Lamu East on Saturday evening.Two of the officers and the women who had sought a lift in the police vehicle sustained serious injuries to their necks and backs.One of the policemen who spoke anonymously said the driver failed to control the vehicle on a narrow bridge."The vehicle slid and plunged into an area very close to the shores where there wasn&rsquo;t much water," he said.The officer said the casualties were taken to a hospital on the island and the vehicle towed to Faze police stationPolice launched investigations to establish whether the accident was deliberate.